		</div>

		<!-- Begin Comments -->
		
		<b>Comment By Cathrine Walters, 10-23-08</b>
		<p>Wildlands CPR, a local conservation non-profit, will have a table at Festival of the Book to promote our Collector's Edition book, "A Road Runs Through It: Reviving Wild Places". With a Foreword by Annie Proulx (The Shipping News, Brokeback Mountain), this passionate collection of essays features writing by Peter Matthiessen (currently nominated for a National Book Award), Barry Lopez, Janisse Ray, Edward Abbey and dozens of others. Together, they explore how roads and off-road vehicles have impacted wildlands, while also offering a restoration vision for these lands.<br />
<br />
Our Limited Edition Set consists of a leather-bound book signed by all 26 living authors including Annie Proulx, Peter Matthiessen and Barry Lopez. The book is accompanied by six woodcut prints by Montana artist Claire Emery in a matching leather clamshell box. We have 47 sets left for purchase.<br />
<br />
Wildlands CPR will be auctioning off one of these sets at their release party and raffle November 7, 2008 at Zootown Brew, 121 W. Broadway St. at 7:30pm.<br />
<br />
Attendees can purchase a raffle ticket for $50 now online, and at Festival of the Book. Attendance not required to win, only 250 tickets available.<br />
Thanks!</p>
		
